com.paypal.merchant.sdk.domain.shopping

Interface TaxRate


  • public interface TaxRate
    TaxRate tracks the name, rate, and id of a tax which you might apply to a CartItem.
    You may have several different tax rates (for example, a tax rate for food and a different tax rate
    for gas). While it is required for a TaxRate object to have a rate, it is not a requirement to set
    a name or id.

    Precision: TaxRates use four points of precision.

    How to create a TaxRate object:

    To have the SDK make a TaxRate object you can use the following factory calls:
    TaxRate myTaxRateObject = DomainFactory.newTaxRate(new BigDecimal("0.1105");
    TaxRate myTaxRateObject = DomainFactory.newTaxRate("Gas Tax", new BigDecimal("0.2500");
    etc.

    Please see the DomainFactory documentation for more details on creating TaxRate objects.
